Ver. 0.19.00 - 2010-11-16
    * The problem with sequential ordering is that there may be many
        unplayed songs which will play straight through.  I rarely want
        to listen to music that way.  The problem with random selection
        is that even a song with a 100 rating might not be selected for
        an indefinite period of time.  I recently saw a 96 rated song
        that hadn't played in 7 months!  This wasn't really a problem
        until we started having 1000s of songs.  Credit Brian Hawkins
        with a very simple and elegant solution to this problem.  The
        program will now calculate a RangeNumber that is TotalEntries
        / 1000 rounded down.  Currently, in random mode, the randomizer
        simply selects a random number between 1 and TotalEntries as the
        entry to look at for age and rating evaluation.  Now, it will
        look in either direction from that random number for RangeNumber
        of entries and select the "oldest" entry.  If TotalEntries <
        1000, then this search won't be done since RangeNumber = 0, so
        the program works just as before.

