Ver. 0.12.00 - 2008-10-15
    * Added Queue window to edit the Queue.  Rightclick, press the Menu
      key, or the F2 key in the Queue window for options.
      Caveat: If there are duplicate entries in the Queue, then Move Up
        and Move Down will always act on the last matching one
        regardless of the actual selection while Delete will always
        act on the first match.  It would require storing some
        redundant information and several extra lines of code and I
        felt it would be a very rare nuisance.  Someone can let me
        know if it is a problem.
      Caveat #2: Avoid making changes in the Queue window if the current
        entry is about to end.  I haven't bothered with locking and it
        could do unexpected things like delete/move the wrong entry.
        Only the queue list would get messed up, so if someone wants to
        try and break it and let me know what happens, please do so.
    * Fixed search highlight in playlist editor.  Finally!  Yay!

Ver. 0.11.00,0.11.01 - 2008-09-22  
    * Added "Rename File" function in playlist editor.  This will change
      the file name both on the disk and in the playlist.
      Caveats:
        1) You cannot change the directory;
        2) You cannot change a name to a file name that already exists;
        3) It does not re-sort the play list until the program is exited
           and re-entered; and
        4) You must have permission to rename the file.
    * Wrote the beginnings of an install script.
    * Fixed a bug where hotkeys sometimes didn't work if NumLock was on.
    * Fixed bug where program would segfault if there was no valid entry
      to play.  Now it just goes into an infinite loop. :)  Well, it
      did, but I fixed that also.
    * Fixed bug where program would segfault after playing the last
      entry in sequential mode.  It now wraps around correctly.
    * Changed so the playlist editor will center on a previous selection
      when changes are made in the playlist.  I'm not sure I got them
      all, though.
    * Moved lock and link flags from lists field to a new flags field.
      This *should* be still backwards compatible.  If you have used
      "Copy to List" to lock or link entries, it will still work except
      it will not take effect until the program is exited and restarted.
      This conversion is automatic but will probably be removed in the
      future.
    * WARNING: Some changes are not backwards compatible with previous
      versions.
        1. The "Link to Next" hotkey in the playlist editor has been
           changed from ^l to ^n.  This is so ^l can be used in the
           future to lock entries.  I have postponed adding the lock
           feature until everyone gets the message of this change.
        2. If you set ratings in the playlist editor, the rating will
           now be locked.  I think that's what most people would want
           anyway.  I may add a button or something to make this
           optional if enough people want it.

Ver. 0.10.01 - 2008-08-21
    * Added "PauseAfter" function.  Couldn't think of a good way to
      work it into the GUI, so it only works by pressing "C".  The
      "Pause" button will have a border and the player will pause
      after the current entry finishes.  You can resume it by pressing
      the Pause button, pressing "c" or "C".
    * NOTE to Ver. 0.10.00 - If you add files while in the "Oldest"
      mode, the new entries will not play until either you exit and
      re-enter omp OR simply type an "o" which will re-sort the oldest
      list.

Ver. 0.10.00 - 2008-08-15
    * Added configuration editor.  I want to keep the program small so
      there is no help in the program.  Most of the options are
      self-explanatory.  Player programs must either be in your
      executable path or the full path must be given.  Note that an
      entry is "selected" using a certain method but may or may not
      "play" based on other criteria.  A letter in parentheses is a
      hotkey that can automatically change the setting of that option.
      WARNINGS:
        Very little error checking is done, so setting certain options
          to invalid values will likely crash the program or cause other
          unexpected behavior.
        If a configuration is saved, the omprc file will be overwritten
          without the comments.  We suggest you keep a copy of the
          original omprc file for reference or in the event it can no
          longer be parsed for some reason.

      Format is: option description | default value | notes
        ogg Player | ogg123 |
        ogg Options ||
        mp3 Player | mpg123 |
        mp3 Options | -v -C --aggressive |
        mod Player | xxmp |
        mod Options ||
        Save Interval | 10 | After this number of played songs, the play
          list will be written to disk.  If set to 0, then the play list
          will never be automatically saved.
        Lists To Play | A | An entry will only be selected if it belongs
          to at least one of the lists given in this option.  Putting in
          a	non-existent list (including nothing) will may cause the
          program to crash.
        Check Rating (%) | true | If true, then when an entry is
          selected, a random number from 1 to 100 is generated.  If this
          number is greater than the entry's rating, then the entry will
          not play.  A queued song will always play.  Note that an entry
          with a rating of 0 can only be played if it is queued
          regardless of this setting.
        Force New | true | No effect if Check Rating is false.  If Check
          Rating is true, then the rating is ignored if the entry has
          never played.  This allows newly added entries that have the
          default rating of 50% to play without checking the rating.
          Once an entry has played at least once, this setting has no
          effect.
        Update Rating | true | If true and the rating is not locked,
          then if the entry plays to completion its rating will be
          increased and if it is skipped then its rating will be
          decreased.  If false, the	rating will not change on either
          of these events.
        Check Repeat (@) | true | See Minimum Age
        Minimum Age | 4h | Minimum amount of time that must elapse
          before an entry is played again.  This is ignored by queued
          songs and only used if Check Repeat is true.
        Selection Method (r)(o) | R | R = Random, S = Sequential,
          O = Oldest.  Whichever method is used, the entry still may
          or may not play depending on options given above.  "R" and
          "S" should be self-explanatory.  "O" will select the entry
          which has not been *selected* (whether played or not) for the
          longest period of time.  Note that the hotkey "r" will toggle
          between Random and Sequential.  The hotkey "o" is used to
          select oldest.  Be aware that selecting the Oldest method
          will cause a one-time delay as the entries are sorted by the
          date.  This will also increase the memory used by	the program.
    * Removed debugging printouts.  What is printed now is either stuff
      I want to see or is output by the players.
    * Playlist editor now displays currently playing song when first
      called up.  A "." will center the editor on the currently playing
      song as well.

