Ver. 0.09.03 - 2008-08-07
    * Ctrl-Escape will exit omp.  [This doesn't work with some
      window managers, so ^w was added in 0.15.00.]
    * Added search option in playlist editor.  Press "/" and enter a
      string to search for.  If the first letter of the string is a "!"
      then the search will be case insensitive.  No regex or anything
      else fancy at this time despite the prompt saying "pattern". :)
      The first entry with that string will be shown.  Pressing "n"
      will find the next matching entry.  For some reason Tk isn't
      doing what I expect and the "active" entry isn't underlined like
      it should be.  So, for now, look at the xterm output to see the
      specific line which is highlighted.  I could "select" the entry
      to highlight it, but I wanted to use the search option to build
      up a select list.  [Fixed in 0.12.00.  I had to modify OCaml's Tk
      interface in order to get it to work. :(  ]
    * Added shortcut keys for playlist editor popup menu options.
      "F2" or the "Menu" key will bring up the popup menu.  Shortcut
      keys are shown in ().  "Escape" will exit the playlist editor.
    * Fixed "Unrecognized file type" for .flac files.  Ahem, when I
      added the flac option I forgot to change the method the program
      used to get the file extension.  The last 3 characters weren't
      ever going to equal "flac".  *blush*  Oh, well, I also saw that
      it always expected lower case extensions as well so that is fixed
      also.
    * Check to see if rating was changed in playlist editor while the
      entry was playing and not update it after entry is played or
      skipped.
    * Changed to not update rating of the currently playing entry if the
      program is exited.

Ver. 0.09.02 - 2008-06-05
    * Changed to not count entries "Not in list" as a skip for forced
      play purposes.  IOW, previously, if 10 entries came up "Not in
      list" the next entry that was in list was a force play regardless
      of rating or time.

Ver. 0.09.01 - 2008-05-31
    * Clear the '=nnn' from playlist entries before running dupe check.
    * Change "Exit" to "Close" on the playlist editor.
    * Add Window title to Playlist.
    * Put directory chooser under playlist window instead of main
      window.
    * Allow large step for ratings that have been changed or locked.
      Actually, this works for all entries.  PageUp will increase the
      rating by 5 more than the normal increase amount and PageDown will
      decrease it by 5 more than the normal decrease amount.

Ver. 0.09.00 - 2008-04-03
    * Changed to use tk_chooseDirectory in the playlist editor.
    * WARNING: This requires a modified OCaml labltk build in order
      to compile.

Ver. 0.08.00 - 2008-03-31
    * Implemented the "Set Rating" popup menu option in the playlist
      editor.

Ver. 0.07.00 - 2008-03-22
    * Added menu and button tooltips.
    * Added "Stop after queue" to the menu.
    * Added "Stop after time" to the menu.

Ver. 0.06.01 - 2008-03-08
    * Update playlist count when new files are added.

Ver. 0.06.00 - 2008-03-07
    * Added ability to play .mod files.  Tested only with xxmp (Debian
      package xmp-x11).

Ver. 0.05.04 - 2008-02-23
    * Added reading of .omp/omprc file to set some of the program
      options.
    * Fixed bug where an entry with a rating of 0 could play in certain
      situations.
    * Fixed "Stop" button.

Ver. 0.05.03 - 2008-02-09
    * Changed so that when rating up/down buttons are pressed, the
      rating is immediately changed so the rating can be locked
      immediately if desired.  This will also save the changed rating
      if the program is exited or the song skipped.

Ver. 0.05.02 - 2008-02-09
    * Added ability to link 2 or more sequential entries together so
      that if the first one plays, the second will follow it.
      Caveat: the linked entries may also come up in the random
      selection, so their ratings will increase faster.
      Workarounds: 1. If you only want the latter entries to play if the
      first entry plays, you can move the latter entries to another
      sublist.  2. If you want them to play alone as well, you can lock
      their rating.
      This feature is implemented by adding the first entry to the "n"
      sublist.  [This has been moved to a "flags" field.]
      2nd caveat: Newly added entries are always appended to the end of
      the playlist until the program is exited.  When exiting, the
      playlist is always sorted.  Therefore, it is best to wait until
      after exiting and restarting the program to link entries together.

Ver. 0.05.01 - 2008-02-09
    * Added ability to change volume with "+" and "-" but only works
      with amixer.  If you see the "Vol: nn%" in the top line, volume
      control should work.

Ver. 0.05.00 - 2008-02-09
    * Added "Lock" button to lock an entry to the current rating.
    * Added "Save" button to save the playlist.

Ver. 0.04.01 - 2008-01-20
    * Added single character commands to allow program control from
      WM's like KDE without having to select the program itself.
      "z" = previous, "x" = play, "c" = pause, "v" = stop,
      "n" = skipdown, "b" = next, (note the previous 2 are in a
      different order on the keyboard than they are in the button
      list), "s" = save playlist
      Debugging/Info: "q" will dump play queue [Changed to "Q"], "h"
      dumps history.  Note that due to threading, the ouput from these
      may be delayed.  Also, your xterm may be messed up when the
      program exits and you'll need to enter "reset" to fix it (or
      "exit" and open another one).

Ver. 0.04.00 - 2008-01-20
    * Added ability to queue entries from the playlist editor.
    * Added "Previous" capability.  One push will restart current song.
      A second push will play the previously played song.

Ver. 0.03.00 - 2007-11-24
    * Added "Add Dir" and "Dupes" functionality to the playlist editor.
      Unfortunately, the Tk directory widget doesn't appear to be
      implemented in OCaml and I don't feel like writing one, so you
      can't browse yet.  You have to enter the path name manually.
      [I'm now using a customized labltk with the directory widget
      working.]  Using "/" for the path name will search your entire
      directory tree for sound files.  Dupes will check for duplicate
      entries based on MD5 encoding.  Note that on a large playlist,
      this can take many minutes (hours?) to run.  [It turns out that
      unless you have a very old computer, this will probably run
      in a few seconds.]

Ver. 0.02.00 - 2007-11-17
    * Added support for multiple sublists.  At present, sublists can
      only be named with a single letter.  Not very flexible, but allows
      one to put entries into various sublists and play only songs
      in a given sublist.  Note that lower case sublists are reserved.
      Specifically "x" is trash, so if you copy/move an entry to that
      list, it will be deleted from the playlist.
      Caveat: Entries that are in the global list "A" as well as a
      sublist or in multiple sublists will increase in ratings faster
      since they can be selected when any of their lists are being
      played.  I have several ideas in mind on how to work around this
      but haven't decided on which one yet.

Ver. 0.01.02 - 2007-10-30
    * Added graphical buttons.

Ver. 0.01.00 - 2007-10-20
    * Ugly gui but with basic functionality.  Generally options can't
    * be changed except by changing the source and recompiling the
    * program.
